    <main class="content">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
        <p>Welcome to Migwani Boys Secondary School. The Migwani Boys Secondary School is an extra County school and the only Boy's boarding school located in Migwani town in Mwingi South Constituency within Kitui county, within the Eastern Region of Kenya. We are committed to providing high-quality education and fostering a supportive learning environment. The school has maintained a good run in performance at the Kenya National Examinations Council, KNEC, exams. In the Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education, KCSE, exams the school posts good results to rank among the best schools in the County.</p>

        <h1 id="academics">Academics</h1>
        <p>Explore our diverse range of academic programs; Computer Studies, Mathematics, English, Kiswahili, Physics, Chemistry, Biology, Business Studies, Geography, History, CRE, Art, Music, etc. Our dedicated faculty members ensure a rigorous curriculum.</p>

        <h1 id="co-curricular">Co-curricular Activities</h1>
        <p>Explore our range of co-curricular activities, including sports, cultural activities, and extra-curricular activities. Our clubs and societies provide a unique and engaging learning experience.</p>
        
        <h1>Admissions</h1>
        <p>Ready to join us? Learn about our admission requirements, application process, and important dates. We look forward to welcoming you!</p>
        
